HEADWORD: Hunkers
<hw>Hun"kers</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Hunker</er>.]</ety> <def>In the phrase <xex>on one's hunkers</xex>,
in a squatting or crouching position; haunches.</def> <mark>[Scot. &
Local, U. S.]</mark></p>

<p><q>Sit <qex>on your hunkers</qex> -- and pray for the bridge.</q>
<rj><qau>Kipling.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

